Fibria Celulose: 1Q Earnings Snapshot Published 19 Hours Ago
SAO PAULO (AP) _ Fibria Celulose SA (FBR) on Wednesday reported first-quarter earnings of $189 million.
The Sao Paulo-based company said it had net income of 34 cents per share.
The fiber pulp producer posted revenue of $1.14 billion in the period.
Fibria Celulose shares have risen 29 percent since the beginning of the year. The stock has more than doubled in the last 12 months.
